AURORA
A CSS library with some add-ons: themes, icons, illustrations, and patterns.

POSTCSS
I wanted to get away with pure CSS, but the DX was bad. I use PostCSS for: imports, custom media queries, CSS variable fallbacks, and auto-prefixing.

WHY CSS?
I'm not here to debate CSS-in-JS libraries. Everything has a drawback.

WHY NOT TAILWIND/TACHYONS/STYLED-SYSTEM/ETC?
I'm not here to debate CSS libraries. Everything has a drawback.